3. Engage in work search activities
The Massachusetts Department of Unemployment Assistance (DUA) requires that as a condition of eligibility you must:
√ Make at least 3 work searches per week. Each work search must be conducted on a different day;
√ Keep a detailed written log of your work search activities. Remember to bring printed completed copies of all Work Search Activity Logs to your Career Center appointments;
√ Provide your work search information to DUA upon request.
